observations.recommendation:
We recommended that management:  

(a) secure a copy of the contract/s and all its supporting documents pertaining to the P1.8 million loan from the LBP and furnish the COA for post-audit purposes; 

(b) require the Municipal Accountant to give a proper and complete accounting (computational analysis of the loan transactions and her basis of taking up) of the Loans Receivable account including the payments received from the Cooperative’s members for the financial assistance granted; 

(c) require the Municipal Accountant to take up the whole amount of financial assistance granted to the Cooperative as loan to include the interest and other bank charges arising from the loan.  Officials and members of the association should be held accountable on the funds received; 

(d) require the submission of lacking supporting documents and enforce liquidation of the financial assistance from the SRCPMPC to avoid suspensions/disallowance in audit; 

(e) conduct review and evaluation of the whole transaction, determine the persons responsible for the consummation of the whole transaction, and if warranted, initiate the filing of appropriate charges against local officials concerned for the violations committed; 

(f) require refunds from persons liable.

We recommend that management:

(a) stop the practice of editing the Daily Time Records. The DTRs to be attached to the paid payroll have to be the original records generated by the biometrics system so as not to defeat its purpose;

(b) instruct the Human Resource Management Office to print the DTRs of all personnel in the municipality and in case of discrepancy, a photocopy of the official logbook have to be attached;

(c )instruct all personnel to log in and out in the biometrics system and in the official logbook as support in case of discrepancies;

(d) install a CCTV camera near the biometrics machine so as to provide additional evidence of actual employee time-in or out, in the event of conflicting data per biometrics printout and official logbook.

We recommend that Management:
(a) direct the Inventory Committee to complete the physical inventory count and submit a copy thereof to this office;
(b) direct the Municipal Treasurer to maintain property cards for PPEs with complete information. These property cards shall be reconciled with other property records like Acknowledgement Receipt for Equipment;
(c) direct the Municipal Accountant to ensure that property subsidiary ledgers contain complete details/description of the PPEs to facilitate proper reconciliation with the inventory report of the inventory committee.
(d) in case of loss of property, the officer immediately accountable thereof, file an application for relief from accountability. Refer to Section 151 of COA Circular No. 92-386 for the documentary requirements to be attached.

We recommend management:
stop the practice of editing the Daily Time Records. The DTRs to be attached to the paid payroll have to be the original records generated by the biometrics system so as not to defeat its purpose;
instruct the Human Resource Management Office to print the DTRs of all personnel in the municipality and in case of discrepancy, a photocopy of the official logbook have to be attached;
instruct all personnel to log in and out in the biometrics system and in the official logbook as support in case of discrepancies;
install a CCTV camera near the biometrics machine so as to provide additional evidence of actual employee time-in or out, in the event of conflicting data per biometrics printout and official logbook.
